descript.abstract: The Indian Claims Commission (ICC) boundary as described in the "Treaty with the Nez Perces, 1855."
descript.purpose: To display the location of the Nez Perce Tribe Reservation boundary as described in Article 2 of the "Treaty with the Nez Perces, 1863."
descript.supplinf: This boundary was mapped by Jack Bell, Director of the Land Services Dept., using 1:100,000 scale Idaho Transportation Department topographic map sheets and digitized with the registration residual mean square error <0.01 inches. Map error at 1:800,000 scale is approximately 670 feet or 0.13 miles.

citeinfo.title: 30x60 Minute Series Idaho Transportation Department Topographic Map

procstep.procdesc:
The Nez Perce Tribe 1855 Reservation Boundary was delineated onto 30x60 minute Idaho Transportation Department topographic quadrangles using the "Treaty with the Nez Perces, 1863 ", Article 2 area description. This description reads as follows:
"Article 2, Commencing where the Moh-ha-na-she or southern tributary of the Palouse River flows from the spurs of the Bitter Root Mountains thence, down said tributary to the mouth of Ti-nat-pan-up Creek thence, southerly to the crossing of the Snake River 10 miles below the mouth of the Al-po-wa-wi River thence, to the source of the Al-po-wa-wi in the Blue Mountains thence, along the crest of the Blue Mountains, thence to the crossing of the Grande Ronde River, midway between the Grand Ronde and the mouth of the Woll-low-how River thence, along the divide between the waters of the Woll-lo-how and Powder Rivers thence, crossing the Snake River 15 miles below the mouth of the Powder River thence, to the Salmon River above the crossing, thence by the spurs of the Bitter Root Mountains to the place of beginning."
Jack Bell, Director of Land Services - GIS Department, digitized this boundary from the Idaho Transportation Department quads to a GIS layer and projected to UTM, units meters, zone 11, datum nad83, spheroid grs1980.
